## 1. `skills/project-loop/SKILL.md`\
\
```markdown\
---\
name: project-loop\
description: Bootstraps config from a project's docs on first run, then runs an\
  autonomous triage -> explore -> fix -> review loop. Project-agnostic and\
  agent-agnostic; all specifics live in loop.config.yml and agent.config.yml.\
---\
\
## Mode check (do this first)\
- If loop.config.yml, agent.config.yml, VISION.md, and LOOP_STATE.md ALL exist\
  -> RUN mode.\
- If ANY are missing -> BOOTSTRAP mode (generate them, then STOP for review).\
\
## BOOTSTRAP mode\
1. Discover the project. Read, if present, in this order:\
   README, /docs, SPEC/design docs, CONTRIBUTING, the package manifest\
   (package.json / pyproject.toml / go.mod / Cargo.toml / pom.xml / etc.),\
   CI config (.github/workflows, etc.), and the test directory layout.\
2. Infer stack + commands from the manifest and CI. Generate loop.config.yml.\
   For any command you cannot confidently infer, write "# TODO: confirm"\
   instead of guessing silently.\
3. Detect the coding agent from config dirs present (.claude/, .codex/, etc.)\
   and fill agent.config.yml's capability map. If ambiguous, list options as\
   TODO; do not pick silently.\
4. Draft VISION.md from the docs (long-term intent ONLY; never put churning\
   status/task lists here \'97 those live in LOOP_STATE.md):\
   - "Core Problem", "Intended Solution", "Target Users", "Definition of good":\
     summarize from README/spec.\
   - "Current Priorities": derive from roadmap/milestones/issues if present;\
     otherwise leave 2-3 TODO slots.\
   - "Non-Goals": pull from any "out of scope" sections; else leave a TODO.\
   - "Core Principles & Constraints" and "High-Level Architecture": infer from\
     manifest, CI, and docs.\
   Never invent content the docs don't support. Mark every inferred item.\
   4b. Pick a VISION.md STYLE based on the detected project type:\
       - single-purpose library/tool -> minimal (tagline + one "why" paragraph)\
       - framework / SaaS / product   -> add Mission, Target Users, positioning\
       - orchestrator / complex tool  -> guardrail "constitution"\
                                         (heavy Non-Goals + Principles)\
       - consumer / narrative app     -> pillar-driven with build standards\
       Default to the guardrail style when unsure. Note the chosen style at the\
       top of VISION.md for the human to confirm.\
5. Initialize an empty LOOP_STATE.md (Open / In Progress / Done / Needs human review).\
6. STOP. Do not start the loop. Present all four drafts, flagging every\
   inferred or uncertain field (and the chosen vision style) for human review.\
\
## RUN mode\
Setup each cycle:\
- Read loop.config.yml (commands, file names, parallelism).\
- Read agent.config.yml (schedule, goal_until, worktree, subagent_dir, connector).\
- Read \{vision_file\} (priorities, non-goals, definition of good).\
- Read \{state_file\} (current work).\
\
Cycle:\
1. Triage: run \{test_command\}; gather recent issues via \{connector\}.\
   Score findings by \{vision_file\} priorities; drop \{vision_file\} non-goals.\
   Write results under "Open" in \{state_file\}, each tagged with the priority it serves.\
2. For each Open finding, up to \{parallelism\} in parallel, each using \{worktree\}:\
     a. explorer (read-only): find root cause, write a brief.\
     b. fixer: minimal change that advances the priority; touch no non-goal.\
     c. reviewer: adversarial check vs \{vision_file\} + \{test_command\} + \{lint_command\}.\
3. Open a PR via \{connector\} ONLY on reviewer approval. Update \{state_file\}.\
4. Send conflicts or non-goal work to "Needs human review".\
\
Stop condition (for \{goal_until\}):\
  every triaged finding is in a PR or escalated, AND \{test_command\} + \{lint_command\} pass.\
```\
