## 3. `agent.config.yml`\
\
```yaml\
# Fill the values for whichever agent you're running. The skill only ever refers\
# to these capability names, so the loop logic never changes when you switch tools.\
capabilities:\
  schedule:     "<run on a cadence>"      # Claude Code: /loop or cron/GitHub Actions | Codex: Automations tab\
  goal_until:   "<loop to a condition>"   # /goal in both Claude Code and Codex\
  worktree:     "<isolate a checkout>"    # Claude Code: --worktree / isolation: worktree | Codex: built-in\
  subagent_dir: "<where role agents live>"# Claude Code: .claude/agents/ | Codex: .codex/agents/\
  connector:    "<reach external tools>"  # MCP (works in both) for issues/PRs/Slack\
```\
